## Deliverable — **Flipbook / burst texture prompt** (per effect)

```text
Seamless game VFX texture OR vertical flipbook strip 8 frames, stylized combat impact, <punch|kick|chord>, crisp sparks, minimal smoke, high contrast, alpha channel as soft falloff, no photoreal fire, no text, 512x512 OR 512x4096 strip, flat lighting, authored for additive blending, John Stick cel brawler style
Negative: photographic explosion, motion blur baked in, watermark, text, gore chunks
Use: Three.js particle soft quad OR mesh decal atlas row N
```

## Deliverable — **Effect spec** (for programmer)

```yaml
effect_id: vfx_hit_<move>_<tier>
spawn_event: onCombatHit
align: along hit normal | camera facing | velocity
lifetime_ms: {flash: 40, debris: 350}
curves: {scale: easeOut, opacity: linear down}
blend: Additive | NormalPremultiplied
mesh: none | ring_mesh | cone_mesh
particles: {count: 12, velocity_inherit: 0.2}
shader_uniforms: {uIntensity: 0–1 accessibility}
pool: burst_pool_01
perf_note: max simultaneous on screen
```

## Working with a non-expert user

Ask: (1) **cartoon vs gritty**? (2) **blood on**? (3) **Target min GPU**?

## Anti-patterns

- **Fullscreen** red flashes for every light punch.
- **Unbounded** decals — **memory leak** in long sessions.
- Effects that **hide** the limb that sold the attack.
